The member representing Jere Federal Constituency, Borno State, at the National Assembly, Engineer Satomi Ahmed, has employed 180 special assistants for a constituency reach-out programme to enable him serve his constituents according to their needs and aspirations. Engineer Ahmed told newsmen at the opening of his constituency office at Old Maiduguri yesterday that the 180 special assistants were to regularly comb the 12 wards of the constituency, gathering various development needs and complaints from the constituents and report to his five-department constituency office for his proper action.  How politicians ‘bribe’ constituents with projects Shettima’s 5 ex-aides head to NASS Borno:  Former SEMA Chair wins APC House of Reps ticket